    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="253" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 668.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-07-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 29, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 16th of July (No.
                            454) has been received, and your proceedings therein are approved. You
                            will be expected to communicate to this department the further decision
                            which Earl Russell has authorized you to look for, in regard to the
                            Virginia, as soon as it shall have been received.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
